ase\\ndef: \\\"A biosynthetic process that results in the formation of ergothioneine from histidine via a set of steps including the hercynylcysteine sulfoxide synthase reaction, which converts N-alpha,N-alpha,N-alpha-trimethyl-L-histidine directly to hercynylcysteine sulfoxide.\\\" [PMID:22209968, PMID:24828577]\\nis_a: GO:0052699 ! ergothioneine biosynthetic process\\n\\n\\nThe child terms map to these two MetaCyc variant pathways:\\nergothioneine biosynthesis I (bacteria) (PWY-7255) = GO:0052704\\nergothioneine biosynthesis II (fungi) () (PWY-7550) = GO:0140479\\n\\nSo, these could be added as exactMatch xrefs to the two child terms.\\n\\nHowever, these specific variant pathways are really beyond scope of GO (they can be represented as GO-CAMs if necessary) so it would be better to obsolete the two child ter... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"Obsoletion request: ergothioneine biosynthetic process terms\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/32018\"\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778466913809,"end":1778466913830}},"id":"prt_e14e37ba9001hJc1mWAwZkCgBm","sessionID":"ses_1eb1c9704ffeHWR5wZvLlt5Vyn","messageID":"msg_e14e369ca001paGtePs4JhQGZC"}}
